info.description: An API for  action that is or was performed on a patient
info.title: Procedure API

get.description:
By passing in the appropriate options, you can search for
available Procedure in the system

parameters.name: skip
parameters.description: number of records to skip for pagination

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: maximum number of records to return

parameters.name: subject
parameters.description: fetch records having the given subject

parameters.name: performer
parameters.description: fetch records having the given performer id

parameters.name: patient
parameters.description: fetch records having the given patient id

parameters.name: part-of
parameters.description: fetch records that are a part of referenced events

parameters.name: location
parameters.description: fetch records that are of given location

parameters.name: encounter
parameters.description: fetch records that are a of given encounter

parameters.name: definition
parameters.description: fetch records that based on given definition

parameters.name: context
parameters.description: fetch records  of a given context

parameters.name: code
parameters.description: fetch records that are a of given procedure code

parameters.name: based-on
parameters.description: fetch records that are a of given based-on object

parameters.name: date
parameters.description: fetch records based on a given date/Period the procedure was performed

post.description: Adds an item to the system

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: Procedure object that needs to be updated to the database

delete.description: This API deletes a Procedure record based on the ProcedureIdn passed
